        "\n",
        "A finite Fourier approximation chooses the best approximation to $f$ from the subspace spanned by finitely many orthogonal sine/cosine or complex exponential functions. The best approximation in $L^2$ is the orthogonal projection, and the Fourier coefficient formulas are exactly projection coefficients.\n",
